Here's a quick tutorial: <br/><strong>1. </strong>To start, prep your nails by filing them into your desired shape and applying a clear or <a href=\"https://amzn.to/3Vllxp3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">neutral base coat</a>. <br/><strong>2. </strong>If you're freehanding, use a <a href=\"https://amzn.to/3K3mf7Y\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">thin nail art brush</a> to paint a curve at the tips of your nails. Fill this in at the top of your nails with <a href=\"https://amzn.to/42veBJK\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">black polish</a> to create that classic French tip design. For an easier route, you can also use French tip <a href=\"https://amzn.to/46iVeon\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">sticker guides</a> or stencils to get that crisp line.<br/><strong>3. </strong>Once that's dry, seal the design with a layer of <a href=\"https://amzn.to/4nt3Qjb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">clear top coat</a> for a glossy finish.
